<reference id="media-controls">
  <title><xmlelement>media-controls</xmlelement></title>
  <shortdesc>The <xmlelement>media-controls</xmlelement> element specifies whether user-interface
    elements are presented to control the playback of the media.</shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>media-controls</indexterm>
        <indexterm>multimedia domain<indexterm>media-controls</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <refbody>
    <section id="usage-information">
      <title>Usage information</title>
      <p>The <xmlelement>media-controls</xmlelement> element is analogous to the
          <xmlatt>controls</xmlatt> attribute on HTML5 media elements.</p>
      <!--<p>The boolean <xmlatt>value</xmlatt> attribute specifies whether the controls should be presented. The default value for this attribute is <codeph>true</codeph>, so the mere presence of this element within <xmlelement>video</xmlelement> or <xmlelement>audio</xmlelement> is sufficient to turn the setting on. The <xmlatt>value</xmlatt> attribute must be explicitly set to <codeph>false</codeph> to specify that controls should not be presented.</p>-->
      <p>If this element is not present, the default behavior is determined by the user agent being
        used to present the media.</p>
    </section>
    <!--<section id="formatting-expectations"><title>Formatting expectations</title></section><section id="processing-expectations"><title>Processing expectations</title></section>-->
    <section id="specialization-hierarchy">
      <title>Specialization hierarchy</title>
      <p>The <xmlelement>media-controls</xmlelement> element is specialized from
          <xmlelement>param</xmlelement>. It is defined in the multimedia-domain module.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="attributes">
      <title>Attributes</title>
      <p>The following attributes are available on this element: <xref keyref="attributes-universal"
        /> and the attributes defined below.</p>
      <dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><xmlatt>value</xmlatt></dt>
          <dd>Specifies whether the media presentation includes user interface controls. The
            following values are recognized:<dl>
              <dlentry>
                <dt>true</dt>
                <dd>Default. Controls are presented.</dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt>false</dt>
                <dd>Controls are not presented.</dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry id="ditauseconref">
                <dt>-dita-use-conref-target </dt>
                <dd>See <xref keyref="attributes-useconreftarget"/> for more information. </dd>
              </dlentry>
            </dl></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><xmlatt>name</xmlatt></dt>
          <dd>The value is fixed to "controls".</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
    </section>
    <example id="example" otherprops="examples">
      <title>Example</title>
      <p>See <xref keyref="video"/> and <xref keyref="audio"/>.</p>
    </example>
  </refbody>
</reference>
